A city in Northern England quickly becoming more and more popular due to its range of shops and bars. It is third largest city in England, behind London and Birmingham. The people of Leeds are often very proud of the fact that they are from the city. Leeds is also home to Temple Newsam and Roundhay Park, two of the countries largest and most beautiful nature parks. Leeds also lays next to the world famous Yorkshire Dales, often known for being the home of soap-opera Emmerdale. Leeds University and Leeds Metropolitan University are two of the most applied for universities in the UK, which also makes Leeds one of the largest student communities in the country.

A person from Leeds is known as a Leodensian, and will quite often be very proud of the title.